</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="index_1autotoc_md7">
<title>Evaluation Model</title>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>Eager Evaluation</bold>: Arguments evaluated before function application</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Partial Evaluation</bold>: Expressions with holes reduce as much as possible</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Environment Binding</bold>: Lexical scoping with closures</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Tail Call Optimization</bold>: (planned) Recursive functions in tail position</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</sect2>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="index_1autotoc_md8">
<title>Special Forms</title>
<para>Special forms have custom evaluation rules and cannot be implemented as functions:</para>
<sect2 id="index_1autotoc_md9">
<title>&lt;tt&gt;if&lt;/tt&gt; - Conditional Expression</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".lisp"><codeline><highlight class="normal">(if<sp/>condition<sp/>then-expr<sp/>else-expr)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Evaluates <computeroutput>condition</computeroutput> first</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If truthy (non-nil, non-zero), evaluates and returns <computeroutput>then-expr</computeroutput></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Otherwise, evaluates and returns <computeroutput>else-expr</computeroutput></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>With holes: returns simplified if-expression</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Examples: <programlisting filename=".lisp"><codeline><highlight class="normal">(if<sp/>(&gt;<sp/>x<sp/>0)<sp/>&quot;positive&quot;<sp/>&quot;non-positive&quot;)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">(if<sp/>?condition<sp/>100<sp/>200)<sp/><sp/>;<sp/>Preserves<sp/>hole<sp/>in<sp/>condition</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="index_1autotoc_md10">
<title>&lt;tt&gt;let&lt;/tt&gt; - Local Bindings</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".lisp"><codeline><highlight class="normal">(let<sp/>((var1<sp/>val1)<sp/>(var2<sp/>val2)<sp/>...)<sp/>body)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Creates new lexical scope</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Binds variables to values sequentially</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Evaluates body in extended environment</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Variables shadow outer bindings</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Examples: <programlisting filename=".lisp"><codeline><highlight class="normal">(let<sp/>((x<sp/>10)<sp/>(y<sp/>20))<sp/>(+<sp/>x<sp/>y))<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>;<sp/>=&gt;<sp/>30</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">(let<sp/>((x<sp/>5))<sp/>(let<sp/>((x<sp/>10))<sp/>x))<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>;<sp/>=&gt;<sp/>10<sp/>(shadowing)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">(let<sp/>((rate<sp/>0.1))<sp/>(*<sp/>?principal<sp/>rate))<sp/><sp/>;<sp/>Partial<sp/>eval<sp/>with<sp/>hole</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="index_1autotoc_md11">
<title>&lt;tt&gt;lambda&lt;/tt&gt; - Function Definition</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".lisp"><codeline><highlight class="normal">(lambda<sp/>(param1<sp/>param2<sp/>...)<sp/>body)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Creates closure capturing current environment</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Parameters bound when function is applied</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Body evaluated in extended environment</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Supports partial application with holes</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Examples: <programlisting filename=".lisp"><codeline><highlight class="normal">(lambda<sp/>(x)<sp/>(*<sp/>x<sp/>x))<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>;<sp/>Square<sp/>function</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">(lambda<sp/>(x<sp/>y)<sp/>(+<sp/>x<sp/>y))<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>;<sp/>Two<sp/>parameters</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">((lambda<sp/>(x)<sp/>(+<sp/>x<sp/>?secret))<sp/>10)<sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>;<sp/>=&gt;<sp/>(+<sp/>10<sp/>?secret)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="index_1autotoc_md12">
<title>&lt;tt&gt;quote&lt;/tt&gt; (planned)</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".lisp"><codeline><highlight class="normal">(quote<sp/>expr)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">&apos;expr<sp/><sp/>;<sp/>Syntactic<sp/>sugar</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Returns expression unevaluated as data</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Useful for symbolic computation</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="index_1autotoc_md13">
<title>&lt;tt&gt;define&lt;/tt&gt; (planned)</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".lisp"><codeline><highlight class="normal">(define<sp/>name<sp/>value)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">(define<sp/>(name<sp/>params...)<sp/>body)<sp/><sp/>;<sp/>Function<sp/>sugar</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Binds value in global environment</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Function form expands to lambda</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect2>
</sect1>
